## User identification

{{IDENTIFY}}

<!--
  When and how user identity is propagated to each SDK. Example:

  - On login success: Sentry.setUser({ id, email }), mixpanel.identify(id).
  - On logout: Sentry.setUser(null), mixpanel.reset().
  - Anonymous users: Mixpanel uses its auto-generated distinct_id; Sentry
    keeps user null.

  Centralize identify/reset in one auth-state hook — do not call from random
  components.
-->

## Common pitfalls

{{PITFALLS}}

<!--
  - Initializing analytics before consent in regions that require it (GDPR).
  - Loading session replay on auth pages where it captures passwords.
  - Hardcoded keys in src/ instead of .env (commit history may leak them).
  - Calling SDK methods before init completes — wrap in `if (sdk.initialized)` or queue.
  - Multiple instances of the same SDK init'd by HMR in dev — guard with a module-level flag.
  - Other gotchas observed in this project's code.
-->
